# Digital Media Service Boundary Rule

This repository is the Digital Media asset management service for the Haderach platform. It provides image storage, metadata management, search, and reference tracking consumed by frontend apps and CMS integrations.

- Keep strict separation of concerns:
  - This repo owns the Digital Media API implementation, storage helpers, embedding/tagging services, and Postgres CRUD.
  - CMS integration (field types, pickers) lives in haderach-cms and consumes this API.
  - Platform orchestration, promotion, and cross-app routing checks remain outside this repo.
- The Digital Media database (`haderach-digital-media` Cloud SQL instance) is private to this service. No other service reads or writes it directly. All access goes through the API.
- Keep service logic and service tests in this repository; do not add platform orchestration logic here.
- Keep naming kebab-case for repo/path conventions; use snake_case for Python modules as language convention requires.
- Prefer explicit docs and small config contracts over heavy scripts or premature automation.
- Use or update docs when behavior/contracts change:
  - `README.md`
  - `docs/architecture.md`
- When adding new structure, keep it minimal and production-minded.
